The paper focuses on image retrieval using deep convolutional features, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed masking schemes and embedding/aggregating methods are specifically designed to address the issue of feature redundancy and improve retrieval accuracy, which falls under information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The inclusion of a hashing module also suggests a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories.
